content.location: A link-up. Begin on Trailer Park and at its 5th bolt traverse straight left passing 1 independent to White Trash's 6th bolt. Finish on White Trash

content.description: Climb up to the roof using huge jugs. After clipping the 2nd bolt, power through the crux deadpoint and continue on sustained edge climbing to the anchors.
content.protection: 7 bolts to 2 shared open shuts. Have a good belayer
content.location: Start directly under the overhang feature on the White Trash Wall

content.description: A short little route that really is only a couple moves long.  One long move at the start that may give some shorter folks a challenge, then a funky shuffle left. Even then, it's a far cry from .11c.  The toughest part of the route is probably forcing yourself to move off of the huge right-facing edge that lines the top half of the climb.  You can keep a hand on this and climb most the route, probably at soft 5.10.
content.location: Goes up the middle of the face.  If it looks too juggy you're too far right, if it's crazy overhanging on nothing holds you're too far left.

content.description: Bubba begins just above water level and climbs up a steep water polished scoop or alcove on large smooth holds, as for Trailer Trash, then moves up and right on the slab with edges and crimps. Higher climb the dihedral to the anchors.
content.location: Right end of the buttress. Right of Trailor Park.
